  "character": "Heterogeneous research testbed. Many partition families covering CPU-only, NVIDIA GPU, AMD GPU, and Intel GPU hardware. Pick the partition for the hardware you intend to use; modules are partition-specific.",
  "notes": [
    "Every partition has its own system module. Always load system/<partition> first, e.g. 'module load system/genoa mpi/openmpi-x86_64'. Never use a system module from a different partition.",
    "source /etc/profile is required in every batch script before any module commands. render_script emits it automatically.",
    "GPU allocation: most GPU partitions require --gpus=<n>. Exceptions: qc-gh200 and ng-dgx-m[0-3] are unified CPU+GPU superchips — no --gpus flag is needed.",
    "ng-dgx-m[0-3] runs Ubuntu; all other partitions run Rocky Linux.",
    "fx700 is Fujitsu A64FX (aarch64-like ARM). x86_64 binaries will not run there. Use r340 for cross-compilation.",
    "qc-gh200 and ng-dgx use aarch64 (NVIDIA Grace). x86_64 binaries will not run there.",
    "Slurm commands require a login shell environment.",
    "No project/account ID is required by default. Jobs submitted without --account will use the user's default Slurm account."
